      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is highly unlikely that your smart devices are directly sensing your emotions like stress or crying. These devices typically rely on environmental sensors like temperature, humidity, or motion. The strange behavior might be related to network interference or a software glitch triggered by subtle changes in your environment when you are upset. Try rebooting both devices and checking for any firmware updates to resolve the unusual synchronization.",
